KCNA Blasts Japan for Its Abduction of Koreans 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Japan is talking much about the "abduction" by someone in a bid to mislead the international community with the second round of six-way talks at hand.
 Its loudmouthed "abduction" is a crafty trick pertaining to Japan to lay an artificial stumbling block in the way of the talks and cover up its true colors as the kingpin of abduction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the past century Japan committed such an extra-large crime against humanity as abducting and forcibly drafting at least 8.4 million Koreans. It has not yet reflected on its past crimes. Of late it went to the lengths of abducting at least 20 DPRK citizens in the Korea-China border area to take them to Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Worse still, the "fund for the relief of north Korean refugees" which is to blame for the abduction is trying to justify its criminal abduction as a "humanitarian aid" as it has become a controversy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The allegation that the crime contrary to international law and the DPRK laws is "humanitarian aid" is a burglary logic that cannot go down with anyone and it cannot but be a target of denunciation by the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is serious is the fact that formal officials of the Japanese government are actively defending the crime of the fund by asserting that it is the duty of the government to protect the victims to the abduction and promote their safety. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While talking much about the already settled issue of the abduction year after year, Japan is keeping mum about its own abduction. This shows what an extent its moral vulgarity and shamelessness have gone to. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is not in a position to slander the DPRK over the issue of abduction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has detained five persons who went to Japan for a hometown visit in violation of the promise made between the governments of the DPRK and Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It itself should be called into question as it is an abduction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's abduction is, in the final analysis, a government-sponsored one, which is a complete perfidy to the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan should ponder over the consequences entailed by the reckless abduction and send the DPRK citizens back at once.

Peasants' Rally Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The "National Peasants' Solidarity" sponsored a rally of peasants from across south Korea in Seoul on February 16 to check the ratification of the free trade agreement at the "National Assembly".
 The rally was held in front of the building of the "National Assembly" and attended by at least 1,400 peasants. The speakers at the rally charged that the government and the political camp are driving 4 million peasants to death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Stating that the conclusion of the free trade agreement precisely means the collapse of the Korean agriculture, they declared that they would fight against the authorities forcing the sacrifice upon the peasants. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day, the peasants, enraged at the news that a "motion on ratification of the free trade agreement" was passed through the "National Assembly," formed a demonstrators' column and tried to enter the building of the "National Assembly," shouting that the struggle has not been ended. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the security authorities called combat police out to suppress them, the peasants battled the police, shouting the slogan "Let's advance into the building of the corrupt National Assembly." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants gathered again to declare that the passage of the motion on ratification of the free trade agreement through the "National Assembly" is null and void and warned that they would wage a campaign to vote down those "assemblymen" who approved the motion in the "general election."

Hanchongryon Issues Statement against Troop Dispatch 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Paek Jong Ho, chairman of the South Korean Federation of University Student Councils (Hanchongryon), was reported to have issued a statement titled "Those who sold out the nation will be made to pay for it" on February 13.
 February 13 will be recorded in the history of the nation as a day of disgrace, the statement said, branding those "national assemblymen" who approved the motion on the troop dispatch to Iraq to meet the U.S. demand as flunkeys who were steeped in pro-Yankeeism to the marrow of their bone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Troop dispatch to the war of aggression and increased cooperation with the U.S. in its war would escalate the war crisis on this land, the statement noted, saying that Hanchongryon calls upon all the south Koreans to wage a more vigorous struggle against the troop dispatch to redeem the nation's disgrace and protect the well-being of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hanchongryon will never forget the national humiliation but certainly force "national assemblymen" who caused it to pay a very high price for it, the statement warned.

Japan Urged to Renounce Hostile Policy toward DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- 11 Mexican political parties and organisations including the Popular Socialist Party on February 13 issued a joint statement to urge the Japanese government to immediately withdraw the "amendment to the law on foreign exchange," make an apology and compensation to the Korean people for the crimes committed by Japan in the past and give up its hostile policy toward the DPRK.
 The statement said that the passage of the amendment through the lower house of the Diet on January 29 is an all-out challenge to the DPRK and it is no more than hysterics of those bereft of reason. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organisations for friendship with the Korean people in Mexico and Mexican political parties express full support for the struggle of the Korean people against Japan's moves to intensify the hostile policy toward the DPRK, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the conviction that the Korean people will win a new victory in their efforts to protect the sovereignty and dignity of the country in the face of the nuclear threat on the part of the U.S. and countries following it.

S. Korean Security Authorities' Inhuman Suppression under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) reportedly issued a statement on Feb. 18 denouncing the south Korean security authorities' inhuman crackdown upon a group of south Korean students congratulating Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the south headquarters of Pomchonghakryon, and Hwang Son, spokeswoman for the Solidarity of Youth and Students for the Implementation of the June 15 South-North Joint Declaration, on their wedding ceremony at Duksung Women's University on February 15. The inhuman crackdown left many wounded.
 Yun has been on the wanted list for six years on the charge of the violation of the "Security Law" and Hwang has already received a police summon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement dismissed it as a never-to-be-condoned act for riot police to enter a wedding place. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tears shed by Yun and Hwang today will help other Koreans harden their will to fight for a reunified country, the statement said, calling for abolishing the SL standing in the way of national cooperation and withdrawing the label of "enemy-benefiting" from Pomchonghakryon.

Japanese Imperialists Hit for Fabricating "Korea-Japan Protocol" 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today runs a signed article one hundred years after the Japanese imperialists fabricated a brigandish "Korea-Japan protocol" on February 23, 1904 in a bid to realize their military occupation and rule over Korea.
 The article describes the protocol as a product of the pressure of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It cites detailed materials to prove that the protocol was a product of the violence, pressure and threat on the part of the Japanese imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The protocol was a criminal document of aggression that provided a "legal guarantee" for the military occupation of Korea under the signboard of "protection," it says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese imperialists secured a springboard to make Korea their virtual colony through the brigandish protocol. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They, basing themselves on it, rigged up "Five-Point Treaty of 1905" and fabricated "Korea-Japan Annexation Treaty" in 1910 to annex the territory of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Shunning the historical facts, the Japanese government is insisting on the "lawfulness" of those treaties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Worse still, the right-wing reactionary forces of Japan assert that Korea-Japan annexation was chosen by Koreans and Japan agreed with various countries of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From the beginning of the year the Japanese chief executive visited the "Yasukuni Shrine" and insisted on the dominium over Tok Islet, betraying the militaristic ambition for reconquest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are seriously mistaken, however. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Korean people today are not what they were yesterday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Japanese reactionaries should put an immediate halt to the shameless distortion of history and honestly apologize and thoroughly compensate to the Korean people for their past crimes.

Pak Pong Ju Meets Delegation of European Parliamentary Assembly 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 22 (KCNA) -- Pak Pong Ju, premier of the DPRK Cabinet, met and had a conversation with a delegation of members of the European Parliamentary Assembly from political parties led by Jacques Santer, former president of the European Commission, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were officials concerned.

U.S. Arms Buildup in S. Korea Condemned
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Group for the Study of Songun Politics sent a letter of protest to the Bush administration on January 31 as regards the U.S. shipment of military equipment into south Korea impeding the improvement of inter-Korean relations.
 The letter vehemently condemned the foolish moves of the Bush administration to ignite a war of aggression against the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter said that as shown by the unjustifiable U.S. war of aggression on Iraq it has become clear again that the U.S. is the very one that unleashed the Korean war in the past. The letter warned that the U.S. will sustain a defeat in Iraq as it did in the Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has put forward rational and realistic proposals for peaceful reunification from long ago, but the U.S. imperialists continue to turn them down in an effort to justify their military colonial domination over south Korea, the letter said, stressing: The DRPK has a legitimate right to have any weapons including nuclear deterrent force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter accused the U.S. of turning away from the just proposal of the DPRK regarding the nuclear issue and extended solidarity to the anti-U.S.,anti-Bush struggle of the National Democratic Front of South Korea and the south Korean people.

KCNA Blasts U.S. Smear Campaign against DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- The United States is persistently spreading a false rumor about the "transfer of nuclear technology" to the DPRK by a Pakistani scientist in a bid to make the story about Pyongyang's "enriched uranium program" sound plausible.
 The February 12 issue of the New York Times again carried misinformation that a Pakistani nuclear expert visited the DPRK more than 10 times at the end of the 1990s to help it in the technology of developing nuclear weapons based on enriched uranium.
 The story about the "enriched uranium program" much touted by the U.S. is nothing but a whopping lie. The US ultra- neo-conservatives fabricated it after having a confab for more than 10 days in the wake of U.S. presidential envoy Kelly's Pyongyang visit in October 2002. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The story is nothing but a poor burlesque orchestrated against this backdrop. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is why the U.S. styling itself "the world's only superpower" has worked so desperately for years to paint the non-existent and unverifiable "enriched uranium program" as truth. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lurking behind it is an ulterior intention to make the international community believe it, scour the interior of the DPRK on the basis of legitimate mandate in a bid to disarm it just as the U.S. did in Iraq and justify its brigandish demand that Pyongyang scrap its nuclear program first at the upcoming six-way talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a trite method of the Bush administration to fabricate false information and violate the sovereignty of independent states under that pretext. The U.S. can not exist without plot-breeding and conspiracy. It is clearly proved by the Iraqi war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is by no means fortuitous that foreign news reports quoted the parties concerned as saying they have never transferred nuclear technology to the DPRK.
 According to the British Financial Times, the Pakistani president officially stated that Pakistan purchased missiles, not nuclear technology from the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK's self-reliant nuclear power industry and its nuclear deterrent force for self-defense were indigenously developed and perfected by scientists and technicians of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK was compelled to change the purpose of its nuclear power industry based on graphite-moderated reactors and possess a nuclear deterrent force for self-defence with a firm determination because the U.S. nuclear threat increased as the days went by and the outbreak of a dangerous war of aggression became imminent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. smear campaign once again forced the army and the people of the DPRK to keenly realize what a just measure it took to build a nuclear deterrent force for self-defence by its own efforts.

Moves for Additional Troop Dispatch to Iraq under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement on Feb. 20 accusing the south Korean "National Assembly" of approving the "motion on additional troop dispatch to Iraq," stirring up a great sensation at home and abroad.
 Driving young and middle-aged people of the same blood into a war of aggression at a time when it is publicly recognized that the Iraqi war ignited by the U.S. is an unilateral war of aggression that cannot be justified with anything is an unpardonable anti-national crime and a wanton violation of justice and peace, the statement said, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The misbehavior of the pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors of south Korea who are yielding to the U.S. demand against  the people's will clearly proves that if the U.S. brings a dark cloud of war against the DPRK to hang over the Korean peninsula under the pretext of the nuclear issue, they will join it without hesitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement called on the south Korean people from all walks of life to turn out as one in a vigorous nationwide struggle to oppose and reject the aggression, interference, strong-arm and highhanded practices of the U.S. that brings misfortune and disasters to the Korean people and resolutely frustrate the moves of the pro-U.S. sycophantic traitors for additional troop dispatch to Iraq.

Japan's Base Anti-DPRK Campaign Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries are escalating their anti-DPRK ruckus, talking a lot about effective sanctions and pressure upon the DPRK and its international isolation.
 Japan's call for "sanctions" and "pressure" under the absurd pretext will only disclose before the world its moral vulgarity and despicable true nature. Rodong Sinmun says this in a signed commentary today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently Japan adopted it as its state policy to apply sanctions against the DPRK by passing the amendment to the law on foreign exchange through its Diet, a law which provides for unilaterally applying sanctions against the DPRK without any UN resolution or international agreement. This is a reckless anti-DPRK hostile act intended to lead the DPRK-Japan relations of hostility and confrontation to the extreme pitch of tension. 
 The Japanese reactionaries should know that if they brandish the old stick of "sanctions" and "pressure" put in their hands by the U.S., toeing its line, it will entail serious consequences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan still remains the sworn enemy of the Korean people. The Japanese reactionaries' increased frenzy will only add to its crimes. This would be little short of putting Japan's security in jeopardy of their own accord. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan is greatly mistaken if it calculates it can wrest something from the DPRK by escalating sanctions and pressure upon it with the six-way talks at hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries should behave with reason, not forgetting the saying as you sow, so shall you reap.

Korean Players Give Good Account of Themselves at 10th ASC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Korean players gave a good account of themselves at the 10th Asian Shooting Championships held in Malaysia from February 10 to 18.
 Merited sportsman Kim Hyon Ung gained a gold medal with 667 points in the men's individual event of 50m pistol shooting, People's sportsman Kim Jong Su with 684 points in men's individual event of 10m air pistol shooting and Kang Un Byol with 575 points in women's individual event of 25m sports pistol shooting (junior). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And Ri Hyang Sun came first in women's individual event of 10m air pistol shooting (junior), Kim Su Ok in women's individual event of 50m rifle 60-bullet prone shooting (junior) and Kim Kwang Hyok in men's individual event of 10m air rifle shooting (junior). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean shooters fetched a total of 6 gold medals at the championships. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
They also won 8 silver medals and 1 bronze medal including two silver medals in men's team event of 25m centre fire pistol shooting and women's team event of trap shooting

Foreigners Visit DPRK Embassies
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 21 (KCNA) -- Prominent figures of different countries paid congratulatory visits to the DPRK embassies in their countries on the occasion of February 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 High-ranking officials of the Democratic Party of Equatorial Guinea including its secretary general paid a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in Malabo on Feb. 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the occasion the secretary general warmly congratulated Kim Jong Il on his birthday on behalf of President Obiang Nguema Mbasogo, founder and chairman of the party, and all its party members, sincerely wishing the fraternal Korean people success in their efforts for socialist construction and peaceful reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Feb. 8 the chairman and the members of the Taekwon-do Association of Bangladesh made a congratulatory visit to the DPRK embassy in their country to present a floral basket before the large statue of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and pay tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Feb. 5 the chairman of the Congolese Group for the Study of Juche Philosophy in Marien Nguabi University visited the DPRK embassy in his country to lay a floral basket before the portraits of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and pay tribute to them.
